commit.message:
Add facerec_ipcamera_knn.py example

Real time facial recognition on ip cameras using knn.

Add files via upload

Real time fast face recognition on ip cameras using knn.
Unpin flake8 so it supports Python 3.8
Drop support for Python 3.4 and add 3.8
Skip a pic if it has none or more than one face
allowed face_encodings to accept either 'large' or 'small' model
fixed leftover worker processes when user requested to end demo

Update list of supported Python versions

The goal of these changes is to provide actual
information about supported Python versions.
I believe that only versions for those you have
tests on CI should be listed as supported.
Applying changes from #826 by chn-lee-yumi manually due to bad git history in PR

Message if no faces in training image

Show a message if a training image contains none or more than one faces
